solution: ```class Solution {
    public int countEven(int num) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= num; i++) {
            int sum = 0, n = i;
            while (n > 0) {
                sum += n % 10;
                n /= 10;
            }
            if ((sum & 1) == 0) count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(num * log10(num))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterate once through every integer up to num, compute digit sum via modulo/division, and count those with even sum. Simple, cache-friendly, and optimal for the given constraint (num ≤ 1000).

